               <p>736. <persName id="def1-736-18440205" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-736-18440205" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-736-18440205" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-736-18440205" type="given" value="ISAAC"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ISAAC BAKER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18440205-736-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440205-736-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440205-736-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing 1 horse-cloth, value 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18440205-name-1170" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1170" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1170" type="surname" value="SKIGGS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1170" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440205-736-offence-1 t18440205-name-1170"></join>Robert Skiggs</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1171" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1171" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1171" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MASON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am carman to Mr. Robert Skiggs, and live in Essex. On the 6th of Feb. my wagon was in Brown's-lane, Spitalfields—I missed a cloth off my horse—I went up to the prisoner's cart, and found it on his cart—he said he did not take it from the horse—he went away, and left his cart with me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He came back? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, in about twenty minutes—when I said to him, "You have taken my cloth," he denied it—I went round his cart, and saw a piece of my cloth hanging from his cart—I took it, and said, "This is my cloth"—he did not say he must have dropped his own cloth—I do not think he had a cloth on his horse—my cloth had not been fastened on my horse—when he came back to me in about twenty minutes, he wanted to know where his cart was—I told him it was gone to the green-yard—I had before called a policeman—I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1172" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1172" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1172" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HUNT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 135.) When I came back from the green-yard the prisoner was at the station—his horse had a sort of leather</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184402050171"></xptr>
               <p>round his loins, but the prosecutor's other horses had cloths on them, much the same as this—I did not see any cloth on the prisoner's cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18440205-736-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
